overshot fixed weir and undershot sluice gate

This is a set of undershot penstock sluice gates and beside it a lock, but only for very small boats and it is nearly always closed. In the middle of the lock there is an overshot radial weir structure. In high winter flow they open the lock gates and just control flow/water level with this radial gate as it is much quicker and easier.
